# Testing Rule: Mandatory TDD Sequence

This repository follows strict TDD for behavior changes. Apply this sequence every time with no exception.

## 1) Required implementation order
1. Write small, single-responsibility, testable functions first.
2. Write unit tests for those functions.
3. Write integration tests next.
4. Provision `.env` for integration tests before execution.
5. Define expected integration-test outputs before implementing app flow wiring.
6. Run tests and make sure all pass.
7. Only then write/update app flow that composes the tested functions.

## 2) Constraints
- Do not start by wiring UI flow first.
- Do not merge behavior changes with missing unit tests.
- Do not skip integration tests when behavior crosses module boundaries.
- Prefer multiple focused unit tests over one long, coupled test.
- Integration tests can be longer and scenario-driven.

## 3) Testability requirements
- Dependencies must be injectable (providers/constructors/interfaces).
- Keep pure logic out of widgets; place in `domain/` or testable app-layer functions.
- Provider-driven logic must support test overrides (`ProviderContainer.test()` and provider overrides).
- Follow Riverpod testing guidance:
  - https://riverpod.dev/docs/how_to/testing
- Provider test baseline:
  - Every provider file in `lib/app/providers/` must have unit-test coverage.
  - For provider tests, use `ProviderContainer.test()` and override external dependencies.
  - Prefer fake/mock dependency providers and fake/mock notifiers for behavior isolation.
  - Keep auto-dispose providers alive during assertions with `container.listen(...)` when needed.

## 4) Completion gates
- `flutter analyze` passes.
- `flutter test` passes.
- New behavior has both unit and integration coverage where applicable.

## 5) Coverage reporting and non-regression
- Generate business-layer unit coverage with:
  - `scripts/report_business_coverage.sh`
- Business-layer scope is fixed to:
  - `lib/app`
  - `lib/domain`
  - `lib/infra`
- Coverage outputs:
  - Markdown report: `coverage/business_layer_unit_coverage.md`
  - Metrics TSV: `coverage/business_layer_unit_coverage.metrics.tsv`
  - Baseline TSV: `coverage/business_layer_unit_coverage.baseline.tsv`
- Rule for pull requests:
  - Do not degrade baseline coverage for `overall` or any `module` row.
  - If an intentional reset is approved, refresh baseline explicitly:
    - `scripts/report_business_coverage.sh --update-baseline`
